millera@genesis.MCS.COM (Alan Miller) writes:
> I was just reading through the PGP 2.1 docs earlier this evening, 
> and something I noticed there might apply--the -m option, which 
> allows display of a message but not saving or any other output.  
> 
> If this were to be a 'subscription' service, each person might 
> receive a version of the picture encrypted with a variation on 
> that, which allows display of the picture with a custom decrypting 
> viewer.

..which the user could still just take a screen snapshot of. don't
rely on -m. even on unix with text output you can always use X or 
screen to copy the output to a file.

